  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nCurrently system messages in group chats appear like regular messages with mentions inside. It's an improvement over the previous UI, but that's not at all how we want them to look like.\r\n\r\n![](https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/626738033701683200/654671507318112276/photo_2019-12-12_14.10.29.jpeg)\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1261\" alt=\"Screenshot 2019-12-12 at 16 12 51\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4932774/70725612-01292a00-1cfd-11ea-9e02-a89fc3a265fe.png\">\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\neach system message is just text centred in the chat thread. 8px margin on all sides. Black for username, Grey for the rest.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"375\" alt=\"Group 44\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4932774/70726377-469a2700-1cfe-11ea-9ef1-1bf8be59396f.png\">\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nand that's how they appear in a chat\r\n\r\n<img width=\"375\" alt=\"Group Chat -_ Someone left chat\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4932774/70726364-439f3680-1cfe-11ea-96d3-1d44abc74b36.png\">\r\n\r\nUsernames are not links, anonymous random names appear without the `@` character preceding them.\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nImplemented according to design. [Link to Figma here](https://www.figma.com/file/aS1ct66VQ6V0cio7vSqS8UoG/Chat?node-id=480%3A361)\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\nThank you!\r\n",
